Xinhua Commentary: Turn outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization - Xinhuanet
Talent is the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talent?
Excellent returning migrant workers are an indispensable new force.
Xinhua News Agency publisher Hai Chunzuo
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26th: Turn outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, lives in Guoyuan Village, Meishan City, Sichuan. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands to return to his hometown to start a business.
After several years of hard work, the annual income of the grape-growing family farm he runs now exceeds one million yuan. He has become a well-known leader in getting rich. He has also been selected to join the village&#39;s &quot;two committees&quot; team.
In recent years, inspired by a series of national policies to support agriculture and benefit farmers, such as poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return to their hometowns to start businesses, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a most populous province in western my country and a major labor exporter, took advantage of the situation and implemented the &quot;Excellent Migrant Workers Reintroduction and Training Project&quot;. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries were produced from the outstanding migrant workers who were introduced back to the country, cultivating village reserve forces. 61,000 people and more than 20,000 party members have been developed, providing a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
Whether you are well-off or not depends on your fellow villagers.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in my country&#39;s rural areas have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have established their own businesses through hard work.
However, objectively speaking, it has also led to the emergence of &quot;hollowing out&quot; in rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grassroots organizations. The village party branch secretaries and party members all show the characteristics of &quot;one old and one young&quot;, that is, aging, low academic qualifications, and the village party The team of organizational leaders is not strong and the problem of lack of support is prominent.
If rural talents and other factors continue to flow to cities in one direction, the countryside will be in a state of &quot;blood loss&quot; and &quot;anemia&quot; for a long time, and revitalization will be empty talk.
Attracting those migrant workers who are capable, aware, and determined to serve their hometowns, guiding them to return to their hometowns to start businesses and become leaders in getting rich, selecting the best among them to train them into party members and rural cadres, and enriching the team of grassroots cadres is the solution to the problem of rural party members. and grass-roots party organizations are in a state of insecurity.
To attract outstanding migrant workers back, we must also ensure that they can stay and work well.
In recent years, Sichuan has begun to pay close attention to the construction of the migrant workers&#39; party. On the basis of strict selection standards, it has established institutional mechanisms such as targeted return of outstanding migrant workers, service guarantees, training and improvement, selection and employment, so that they can improve their abilities and work. There is security in school, hope in life, true roots in the countryside, and a sense of accomplishment in starting a business.
This year is the final year of the decisive battle against poverty. Talent is the key factor in connecting poverty alleviation with rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels must attach great importance to the group of outstanding returning migrant workers, and through comprehensive measures, build them into a work team and a new force that can be retained, can fight, and cannot be taken away, so as to provide support for rural poverty alleviation and development and revitalization. Strong organizational guarantee and talent support.
