Hurricane Hanna&#39;s landfall in Texas may cause swollen rivers and flash floods - China News Service
China News Service, July 26 (Xinhua) Comprehensive foreign media reports said that at 5 pm local time on the 25th, Hurricane &quot;Hanna&quot; landed in Texas, USA. It will bring strong winds and rains to Texas, swollen rivers, and may also trigger life-threatening flash floods. .
