&quot;Fortress Jiangnan&quot; pursues the poetic &quot;Yellow River Dream&quot;-China News
(Story of Poverty Alleviation in China) &quot;Crossing the Yangtze River&quot; pursues the poetic &quot;Yellow River Dream&quot;
China News Service, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) &quot;The Yellow River has thousands of miles of sand, and the waves and winds blow from the end of the world.&quot;
The Yellow River, which aroused the passion of countless literati, gave birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Today, Ningxia, known as the &quot;Fortress of Jiangnan&quot;, is adhering to the concept of &quot;ecological priority, green development&quot; and pursuing the poetic &quot;Yellow River Dream.&quot;
The &quot;Dream of Blue Waves&quot; with Clear River and Beautiful Water
&quot;The Yellow River in the world enriches Ningxia&quot;. The Yellow River flows through Ningxia for 397 kilometers and is the &quot;mother river&quot; that nourishes the country.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization, management and protection of rivers and lakes are out of balance, and chaos such as excessive sewage discharge, lake reclamation, and water encroachment have emerged, resulting in black and smelly water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment, and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting diversified restoration of water ecology and striving to make the Yellow River beautiful and clear.
Water control must start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopts the approach of &quot;raising standards + pollution control + strict management&quot;. All sewage in industrial parks has been treated centrally, all urban sewage treatment plants have achieved Class A discharge standards, and black and odorous water bodies in urban built-up areas have been basically eliminated. The application was successfully submitted. The third batch of China’s black and smelly water body demonstration cities.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake chief system in 2017, and now has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake chief responsibility system in districts, cities, counties, and villages, and long-term river and lake patrols have become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, lives in a village beside the Yellow River. He has witnessed the changes in the Yellow River: &quot;The water used to have a smell, but after treatment, the smell is gone.&quot;
Gu Jincheng said that with the improvement of the ecological environment, his life has become more comfortable. Now he and his family often go for walks along the Yellow River to feel the clear water and blue sky.
The “wetland dream” of flying sand gulls
Birds, green trees, plank roads, clear water... the beautiful scenery of &quot;Gathering of Sand Gulls&quot; written by Fan Zhongyan has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, and various wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands, and swamp wetlands have been formed along the way. It plays an important role in promoting the rational utilization of water resources and aquatic ecological balance. It has also become an internationally important bird migration channel.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested a total of approximately 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. Currently, Yinchuan wetland area is 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and swamps, and There are 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region-level wetland parks, and 8 municipal-level parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of the Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds. “The relict gull is an endangered bird, with only more than 20,000 in the world, among which Yinchuan Wetland has More than 2,000 live there.”
At the same time, Ningxia has delineated a 500-meter red line for the wetland protection areas on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law. It is stipulated that except for public welfare projects, no unit or individual is allowed to carry out development, construction and business activities within the protection scope.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through pollution source control, comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology, and construction of terminal wetlands, the water quality of Ningxia’s nine main drainage ditches has now reached 100% Class IV standards. “The water is now clear. The fish are swimming and the flowers are blooming.”
The “drinking water dream” that benefits people’s livelihood
Yinchuan City in Ningxia once had an &quot;embarrassing&quot; title: it was the only city along the Yellow River that &quot;guarded the Yellow River for lack of water.&quot;
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing a persistent water shortage problem during the peak summer period. The &quot;pain of water shortage&quot; in the past ten years has become a painful summer experience for many high-rise residents. However, major water sources are at a super high level. With the mining limit and a large area of groundwater over-exploitation funnel area formed underground in the urban area, water source shortage has become a problem plaguing Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified Yellow River water has become a good solution to the drinking water problem of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of the Yinchuan Municipal Water Affairs Bureau, said that in order to improve the demand for living and production water for urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia promptly launched the urban and rural western water supply project in the Yinchuan metropolitan area to replace the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
&quot;On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially opened water to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank Yellow River water. &quot;
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan water conservancy department will make overall plans to integrate the transformation of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply. “In the next step, we will integrate the scattered water supply points in rural areas and connect them all to the western water supply project. It is expected that by the end of this year, the Yinchuan area will be basically completed. Integrated water supply for urban and rural areas.”
