Four departments launch a new round of App governance to protect personal information security-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, July 25 (Reporters Yu Junjie and Chen Aiping) Reporters learned from the Cyberspace Administration of China on the 25th that the governance work on illegal and illegal collection and use of personal information by Apps in 2020 has been officially launched recently, focusing on cracking down on the unauthorized uploading of personal information in the background of Apps, etc. An issue that has received strong public response.
It is reported that this round of App governance work was carried out jointly by the Cyberspace Administration of China, the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology, the Ministry of Public Security, and the State Administration for Market Regulation.
According to reports, the special governance working group composed of four departments accepted more than 12,000 valid reports from netizens last year and conducted verification on more than 2,300 apps. For 260 apps with large user bases and outstanding problems, public exposure and about Negotiation, removal and other punitive measures.
According to the relevant person in charge of the Cyberspace Administration of China, the number of apps currently exceeds 5 million, and the problem of illegal collection and use of personal information has not yet been fundamentally resolved.
Governance work will be further intensified in 2020. Based on App verification, the scope of governance will be further expanded to include SDKs (software development kits) and small programs.
It is reported that the working group will conduct special research and in-depth inspections on issues such as irregular collection and use of personal biometric information and abuse of sensitive permissions by apps, focusing on background permission abuses such as recording and taking photos.
Based on the circumstances of the problem and the severity of the consequences, the working group will issue interviews, warnings, removals, fines and other penalties in accordance with laws and regulations to form an effective deterrent to violations of laws and regulations.
It is understood that the working group plans to formulate and issue application store review and management guidelines for the collection and use of personal information by apps, to guide and urge app stores to effectively conduct pre-launch review of apps and strictly control access.
In addition, the working group will also release free technical tools to guide small and medium-sized enterprises to conduct self-assessments and improve the legal compliance of personal information collection and use activities of small and medium-sized enterprises.
