The longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir area is completed-China News
2020-07-26 17:34:48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel.
Photo courtesy of China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Corporation
China News Service, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on the 26th that the 18.9-kilometer-long Zhengdu-Wanzhou High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel was fully completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Little Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed rail tunnel within the Three Gorges Reservoir Area, but also the longest single-hole, double-track high-speed rail tunnel currently under construction in China with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour.
The Zhengzhou-Wanzhou high-speed railway is located in the three provinces and cities of Henan, Hubei and Chongqing. It connects the Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan high-speed railways in the north of Zhengzhou, and connects the Chongqing-Wanzhou high-speed railway in the south of Wanzhou to Chongqing. It is a channel along the river and part of my country&#39;s &quot;eight vertical and eight horizontal&quot; high-speed railway network. An important part of the Hunan Channel.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel of the Zhengzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railway was fully completed on the 26th.
The picture shows the penetration site.
The Zhengzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railway starts from Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, and Xiangyang City, Hubei Province to Wanzhou District, Chongqing City. The newly built line is approximately 818 kilometers long, with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and is approximately 184 kilometers within Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou to Xiangyang section was put into operation in advance on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel, which was fully completed on the 26th, is a control project for the Zhengzhou-Wanzhou High-speed Railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing City. It has a total length of approximately 18.9 kilometers and a maximum burial depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel started in February 2017 and was fully completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Guojun, the person in charge of the Zhengzhou-Wanzhou high-speed railway tunnel design of China Railway Eryuan Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the surveyor and designer, the terrain and geological conditions of the location of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel are very complex, and it faces risks such as karst, sudden mud and water, and large deformation of soft rock. Class I high-risk tunnels are extremely difficult to design and construct.
&quot;During the construction of the project, we used geological survey methods, geophysical prospecting methods and advance drilling methods to conduct advanced geological forecasts, and adopted special design plans for more than 30 caves of various types. For example, we designed and built a 24-meter-long bridge across the tunnel. Large karst caves with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters can prevent tunnel settlement,&quot; Wang Guojun said.
According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, the construction company, during the construction of the tunnel, a combination of dredging and blocking was adopted. By building horizontal tunnels and horizontal guides, grouting and water blocking, strengthening tunnel structural support and building sewage treatment stations, it ensured the orderly progress of the project. , it also avoided construction drainage damage to the water body of the Little Three Gorges Scenic Area, and at the same time successfully overcame construction problems such as 7-kilometer-long soft rock major deformation and other unfavorable geology, and multiple muddy water inflows with a maximum daily water inflow of 157,000 cubic meters. .
After the Zhengzhou-Wanzhou high-speed railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger transportation channel from southwest my country to the Central Plains, North China, and Northeast China. It will play an important role in improving the capacity and quality of the northeastern railway channel in southwest China, improving the layout of the regional road network, and accelerating tourism along the route. It is of great significance to promote resource development and urbanization process, promote coordinated regional development, and promote the implementation of the Western Development Strategy.
