The picture shows Wu Na (left), president of Beijing Houdeli Bee Industry Co., Ltd., promoting Qinghai bee products.
Photo by Ma Mingyan
China News Service, Qinghai and Hainan, July 26th: Title: &quot;Sea of Flowers Live Broadcast Room&quot; by Qinghai Lake: &quot;Sweet&quot; sales help farmers increase income
Author Hu Guilong Pan Yujie
“In midsummer, Qinghai Lake is full of golden flowers and thousands of bees flying around. The altitude here is high, the temperature difference between day and night is large, and there is less air pollution. The strong light breeds the most tenacious and generous bee colonies, creating Qinghai royal jelly with high activity, high protein, and richness. Contains nutritional value, low sugar and low fat features.”
Zhang Jianxun, deputy director of the Industrial and Information Administration Bureau of Hainan Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture, Qinghai Province, said on the 26th.
On the same day, the bee products live broadcast event &quot;Fighting the Epidemic Together to Help Farmers&quot; was held on the banks of Qinghai Lake. The China Bee Products Association, entrepreneur representatives, beekeepers and other parties gathered to promote Qinghai&#39;s characteristic bee products, with a total online and offline sales of nearly Ten thousand bottles of Qinghai Plateau royal jelly, with a total value of nearly 3.8 million yuan.
The picture shows beekeepers displaying bee products on site.
It is reported that this live broadcast event uses the Beijing Houdeli Bee Industry chain store network, Kuaishou, Taobao and other well-known domestic bee product retail companies, live broadcasts, and e-commerce platforms to promote exchanges and cooperation between &quot;enterprises + beekeepers + growers&quot;, and &quot;Qinghai Plateau Spring Jelly Consumption Vouchers&quot; are continuously issued to consumers through online and offline channels, and the company is expected to make a total profit of nearly 5.28 million yuan throughout the year.
In this regard, Wu Na, president of Beijing Houdeli Bee Industry Co., Ltd., believes that it is &quot;very worthwhile&quot;: &quot;This move can expand the popularity of Qinghai bee products, attract more consumers to understand and like pure and natural bee products without additives, and drive the popularity of bee products.&quot; Increase agricultural income.”
At present, the company has signed a production cooperation strategic agreement with Qinghai Yun Bee Industry Co., Ltd. and Qinghai Huabao Bee Industry Co., Ltd., hoping to jointly promote the rapid development of Qinghai’s local bee industry.
The picture shows the sea of rapeseed flowers on the banks of Qinghai Lake.
This spring, due to the need to set up road barriers for epidemic prevention and control, beekeepers&#39; pursuit of flowers and nectar was blocked. Many bees died due to missing the flowering period and lack of food, and beekeepers&#39; income was seriously affected.
“Throughout the year, beekeepers travel long distances to follow the flowering season, moving all the way north from Yunnan and Sichuan to the northwest region. They live in the open and have no fixed residence, which is very hard.
As businesses, we have a responsibility to help them. &quot;
Wu Na said.
&quot;Little bees are &#39;environmental scouts&#39;, and bees cannot survive in heavily polluted areas.&quot; Zhao Xiaochuan, executive vice president of the China Bee Products Association, said that bee pollination is an important link in the ecological chain and plays an important role in protecting plant diversity and improving ecology. The environment plays an irreplaceable role.
At the same time, bee pollination can increase crop yields and improve quality. Especially in areas with extensive planting and poor management conditions, pollination is of greater significance.
Research data shows that pollination can increase rapeseed production by about 15% - 30%.
The picture shows Zhao Xiaochuan (right), executive vice president of the China Bee Products Association, promoting Qinghai bee products.
&quot;The economic, ecological and social benefits created by bee pollination are far greater than the value of bee products themselves. The bee industry has huge potential in human health, crop production, vegetation reproduction, and ecological protection, but people have always known very little about it.&quot;
Zhao Xiaochuan said.
Nowadays, there are fewer and fewer beekeepers. In addition to beekeepers who travel all year round, there are also many poor households with limited mobility who choose to use beehives to invest in cooperatives.
&quot;The state has financial support, and we contacted technical personnel for help and guidance. Beekeepers lack understanding and judgment of the market environment. To open up sales, we need help and coordination from the government, enterprises, and industry associations.&quot;
Zhao Xiaochuan said.
&quot;I hope everyone will pay more attention to and help beekeeping groups in the future,&quot; Wu Na said. &quot;Our bee products are also screened and controlled strictly in accordance with national standards to ensure quality and protect the rights and interests of consumers while helping beekeepers.&quot;
