Time passed by, the altitude continued to rise, the oxygen content became lower and lower, and the physical strength continued to be exhausted. These factors tested the will of the patrol members.
They gritted their teeth and persisted, stepping over several landslides and crossing several dangerous shoals.
At about 16 o&#39;clock, it was lunch time for the patrol members. They took out their own dry food and sat down at an altitude of more than 5,700 meters, accompanied by rain, sleet and snow, to replenish their strength with food.
Soldiers at the Banong Chok Kang sentry point undergo tactical and physical training.
During the break, they would play cards together, and the loser would do push-ups, which was both entertainment and physical exercise.
After a short rest in the cold wind, they climbed up to the patrol target point, took out the national flag on the mountain pass, and solemnly swore an oath.
Behind them are the snow-capped mountains, and in front of them is dozens of kilometers of no-man&#39;s land. They are the safest guardians of the country.
