Before filling in the volunteer application form, you should first understand what the professional level difference is - China News Service
2020-07-27 02:22:36 Source: Chongqing Morning News Author: Yu Xiao Editor: Yu Xiao
Before volunteering to fill in the application form, first understand what the professional level difference is.
Every year when filling in the college entrance examination application form, there are students or parents who do not understand the terms involved in the application form, which in turn affects the application process.
This year, five universities, Beijing Jiaotong University, University of Science and Technology Beijing, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University, and Beijing University of Chemical Technology, jointly released the 2020 admissions policy to eliminate professional differences.
What does professional level difference mean, and what is its significance in filling out volunteer applications?
There are three ways to assign majors
Experts remind you that before filling in your application, you must carefully read the &quot;Admissions Regulations&quot; of your favorite school and understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including transfer ratios, major allocation rules, etc.
The major allocation rules refer to the three main methods for major admissions after colleges and universities adjust their grades: major priority, score priority, and major grade difference.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be specified in the &quot;Admissions Regulations&quot;.
However, there are also some colleges and universities whose admission principle is based on total score priority, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, candidates within the admission range will be queued according to their total scores. When the scores do not reach the admission score for the first major, it will be seen whether they have reached the admission score for the second major, and so on until the last major is admitted. There is no level difference between them.
The so-called &quot;major level difference&quot; means that when the school arranges the candidates&#39; majors, it determines the admission majors for candidates in different majors based on one or several scores published in the admissions regulations. This score is the &quot;major level difference.&quot;
That is, the difference in scores between colleges and universities when admitting candidates’ first major preference and non-first major preference, and the grade difference scores between each major preference, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
for example.
Assume that student Xiao Ming applies for college A and scores 560 points. His major preferences are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, and e-commerce. The major admissions of college A adopts the professional grade difference method. The grade difference is 2 points and 1 point. , 1 point, 0 points.
When making major assignments, if Xiao Ming’s first major choice meets the major admission requirements and the major has planned balance, then Xiao Ming will be admitted to the “Computer Science” major; if Computer Science is not admitted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points , ranked according to the score of 558 points with the candidates who applied for the first major &quot;International Trade&quot; to determine whether they meet the major admission conditions; if they still cannot meet the major admission requirements, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 557 points) for the third major &quot;Automation&quot; &quot;Admission; if it still cannot be satisfied, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 556 points) for admission to the fourth major. If the subsequent major still cannot satisfy the professional preference, no points will be reduced, and so on.
Different university majors have different settings
With the popularity of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have now abolished the professional level difference, but this year some colleges and universities still retain this method. Judging from the &quot;Enrollment Regulations&quot; announced by each school, this year there are mainly more than 20 universities that have set up A professional level difference.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight Academy, etc.
Among these universities, each university has different professional levels.
Some colleges and universities have grade differences for each major, such as Ningxia University. Candidates whose files have been submitted to the school will be admitted according to the order in which the candidates fill out their major preferences by 1 point in descending order.
Some universities have set different professional levels between different majors.
For example, at Jimei University, the total score difference between majors is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first major and other majors is 3 points. There is no gap between other majors and is regarded as a parallel choice. The majors between other majors and transferred majors are The grade difference is 1 point.
When filling in the application form, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the school they are applying for to see if there is any professional grade difference and what the form of the grade difference is. While fully considering the scores, they must also reasonably analyze the school and major they intend to choose. , if the institution clearly adopts the grade difference method for admission in the admissions regulations, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between majors when choosing a major to increase the chance of admission.
