Qiu Tenghua made the above remarks while participating in the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) trade ministers&#39; video conference on combating the new coronavirus epidemic held on the 25th.
During this meeting, the participating ministers exchanged views on the substantive plans that APEC can take to respond to the impact of the COVID-19 epidemic and promote economic recovery in the region.
Qiu Tenghua said that the public health and economic crisis triggered by this epidemic has had an unprecedented and far-reaching impact on society and the economy.
“We are in a dual battle. We must first defeat the epidemic before we can restore the economy.
We must have a clear goal. The virus is our common enemy. Only by cooperation can we win. Otherwise, we will only fail. &quot;
Qiu Tenghua said that the series of trade restrictions triggered by the new coronavirus epidemic will not help control the epidemic.
Trade is a key solution to current problems and should not be seen as the problem.
He condemned all discriminatory and polarizing policy measures and urged all economies to keep their borders open at this critical moment, maintain the smooth operation of supply chains, and avoid erecting trade barriers or adopting irrational trade policies.
Florida has confirmed 414,000 new coronavirus cases, becoming the second most severely affected state in the United States - China News Service
China News Service, July 26 (Xinhua) Comprehensive report: The website of Johns Hopkins University in the United States shows that as of about 8:34 on the 26th, Beijing time, Florida, the United States, has reported more than 414,000 confirmed cases of COVID-19, exceeding the number in New York State. 411,000, making it the second largest &quot;epidemic area&quot; in the United States after California.
The Florida Department of Health said on the 25th that Florida reported 124 deaths on the 24th.
This is the tenth time since the start of the COVID-19 pandemic that Florida&#39;s daily death toll has exceeded 100.
It is reported that the total number of cases in Miami-Dade County, Florida&#39;s most severely affected county, has exceeded 100,000.
There are currently 8,974 COVID-19 hospitalizations in Florida, 1,874 of which are in Miami-Dade.
Since July 4, hospitalizations for COVID-19 in the state have increased by 79%.
Since the first U.S. state reopened on April 24, 91,000 lives have been lost to COVID-19.
According to data provided by Johns Hopkins University, the total number of confirmed cases reported in the United States has reached 4.176 million, with at least 146,000 deaths.
People in Chengdu gathered to watch the US Consulate, but police stopped people from &quot;looking too happy&quot;
In response to the U.S. closing the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, China announced on Friday the closure of the U.S. Consulate General in Chengdu.
On Saturday, the U.S. Consulate&#39;s badge was removed, and on Sunday, a car with dark glass drove away from the consulate amid boos from passers-by.
On Sunday, many Chengdu people gathered in front of the U.S. Consulate to take photos, and people who had never been there also came to take a look out of curiosity about current events.
A reporter from AFP’s Chengdu station also went to observe the area near the US Consulate in Chengdu. News came back that there was an endless stream of curious people, and many parents took their children to take a walk to view the consulate, take photos of the building, or take selfies.
The consulate was surrounded by guards, and the police &quot;corrected&quot; people&#39;s behavior from time to time. They seemed not to allow any abnormal behavior: a woman was stopped just as she was about to sing a popular song, and a guard confiscated a banner.
But residents of a nearby residential building successfully pulled up a giant Chinese flag on their balcony and shouted slogans in support of China.
The U.S. Consulate in Chengdu opened in 1985 and covers all U.S. consular-related matters in southwest China, especially the Tibet Autonomous Region.
A reporter from AFP’s Chengdu station said that the Chinese government’s response to the United States has been relatively restrained: many Chinese people online asked the government to close the U.S. Consulate in Hong Kong, but the official only said that “closing the U.S. Consulate in Chengdu is an unreasonable act against the United States.” Necessary and lawful response.”
Currently, in addition to Chengdu, the United States has consulates in Guangdong, Shanghai, Shenyang, Wuhan, and Hong Kong in China.
The large-scale integrated media operation &quot;Watch Poverty Alleviation through Live Broadcasting in Villages&quot; starts - Today&#39;s News - Hunan Daily - Huasheng Online
Hunan Daily · New Hunan Client, July 25th (Reporter from this newspaper) On July 25th, the large-scale integrated media action &quot;Village Live Broadcast to See Poverty Alleviation&quot; hosted by the China Central Radio and Television Station Financial Program Center started from Xuzhou, Jiangsu Province. A caravan carrying a 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system slowly drove out of the venue under the watch of guests present.
General Secretary Xi Jinping pointed out that “2020 is a milestone year. We will build a moderately prosperous society in all respects and achieve the first centenary goal. 2020 is also the year of decisive victory in the fight against poverty.”
The large-scale integrated media campaign &quot;Watching Poverty Alleviation via Live Broadcast in Villages&quot; is an important measure taken by the Financial Program Center of China Central Radio and Television to coordinate with this major theme and promote the fight against poverty.
This action will visit poverty alleviation villages in more than 20 provinces, autonomous regions, and municipalities across the country, unearth fresh stories of poverty alleviation, directly examine the dramatic changes in the appearance of the village, and show how the villagers break through the difficulties of survival and development and move towards wealth.
This operation will last more than 3 months.
The reporter started from Xuzhou and divided the troops into two routes. One route took the southwest route, passing through Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Chongqing, Yunnan, Tibet and other places; the other route took the northwest route, passing through Henan, Shaanxi, Gansu , Qinghai, Xinjiang, Ningxia, Inner Mongolia, Shanxi, Hebei and other places, with a journey of more than 10,000 kilometers.
In terms of reporting format, &quot;Village Live Broadcast to Watch Poverty Alleviation&quot; boldly integrates.
The economic development of the villages visited by the caravan will be broadcast through CCTV Financial Channel, CCTV Economic Voice, China Transportation Broadcasting, and CCTV Financial New Media.
Among them, the live TV broadcast will mainly be completed on CCTV Financial Channel’s noon news program “World Finance” (first broadcast time: Monday to Sunday 12:00-13:00), and CCTV Financial Channel’s prime time news program “Economic Information Broadcast” will Create a poverty alleviation reporting column (first broadcast time: Monday to Sunday 20:30-21:30).
At the same time, the caravan will broadcast a one-hour live broadcast on the CCTV Finance client for each village it visits. Viewers can watch the live broadcast and participate in the lottery by downloading the CCTV Finance APP.
In terms of technology application and studio design, &quot;Village Live Broadcast to Watch Poverty Alleviation&quot; has the courage to make breakthroughs and pioneered the &quot;outfield new media caravan&quot;.
The car is equipped with a 5G new media mobile cloud production and broadcasting system, using 5G+4K/8K+AI technology to achieve the organic combination of online and offline, large and small screens, and television broadcasting.
It is equipped with a Sanxun studio area. The studio area is modified from a container and is 12 meters long, 2.55 meters wide and 3.98 meters high. The box adopts a hydraulic automatic expansion structure and can be turned up to 120 degrees.
The studio area can also be automatically expanded and connected to an external expansion platform, covering an area of more than 50 square meters, which can meet the scene requirements of most programs.
It is already hot summer in Dongchuan District, Kunming City, and what is even hotter than the weather is the poverty alleviation workshop next to the relocation site.
Lu Ling, an employee of Kunming Esif Electronic Technology Co., Ltd. said, “Now, as soon as I leave home, I enter the factory door, making money and taking care of my family at the same time, thanks to the free vocational skills training organized by the labor union.”
Walking into the electronic component processing poverty alleviation workshop in Tongdu Street, Dongchuan District, a bustling and busy scene comes into view.
Lu Ling, who is in her 40s, is a single mother, raising her children by herself and taking care of her elderly parents.
When she was in the most difficult time, the Dongchuan District Federation of Trade Unions helped her come up with ideas and solutions, providing help in times of need.
Since 2018, Lu Ling has enjoyed assistance policies such as housing, schooling, social security, and employment, as well as subsidies from trade unions at all levels.
This year, her children have successfully graduated and are employed. She herself also has a job and income after participating in skills training, and she was out of trouble at the end of April.
It is reported that the Dongchuan District General Organization’s special skills training project to assist in poverty alleviation is part of the skills training work of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions.
Based on the characteristics of the difficult workers in the relocation site for poverty alleviation in the district, the district general manager conducted an in-depth investigation to understand the training needs and determined the types of training jobs. In the near future, it plans to train a total of 450 electricians, welders, and pastry chefs.
Recently, Li Yi, an employee of the Agricultural Bank of China Yunnan Menglian County Branch, wrote a sincere letter of thanks to the County Federation of Trade Unions.
In her letter, she sincerely thanked the union for the Golden Autumn Student Aid given to her from August 2013 to January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi&#39;s father died in a car accident, and her mother was included in the file of employees in need. Since then, she has been enjoying the care of the file and card policy.
With the help of the local trade union, Li Yi successfully completed her studies.
Since 2016, 3,809 households have been lifted out of poverty through institutional guarantees and targeted assistance.
The successful rescue of Lu Ling&#39;s family and Li Yi is a microcosm of Yunnan&#39;s trade union&#39;s work to promote the relief of employees in need.
According to Duan Kaiyuan, a staff member of the Legal and Rights Protection Department of the Yunnan Provincial Federation of Trade Unions, the Provincial Federation of Trade Unions has strengthened the dynamic management of files for employees in need, promoted the normalization of file creation, and promptly included employees in need who meet the conditions for file creation into the assistance system; broadening the scope of employees in need As for the application channel, WeChat is used to open an online filing service platform for employees in need to facilitate timely and proactive reporting by employees in need.
During the epidemic, it was difficult for migrant workers to go out to work. In order to help employees in need relieve their life pressure, Yunnan Province arranged a total of more than 13 million yuan to send warm funds. According to the standards of 2,000 yuan per household for employees in need at the national level and 1,500 yuan per household for employees in need at the provincial level. , carried out special warm-hearted condolences activities to more than 6,000 national-level and more than 1,000 provincial-level employees in need.
At the same time, the provincial headquarters connects with various Internet recruitment platforms such as the human resources and social security departments and Zhaopin Recruitment to push recruitment information to employees in need and provide employment consultation, employment guidance and other services.
